Below is a systematic breakdown of how the target model is built and which blocks (by index) match each piece.  The final section shows a reasonable step‐by‐step order in which you could assemble them.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1.  DESCRIPTION OF THE TARGET STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Overall Count and Layers
  – There are 20 total blocks arranged into two main “sections”:  
    – Left Section: 8 blocks in five layers (counting from the bottom up).  
    – Right Section: 12 blocks in (effectively) three layers plus a few tall uprights.

• Left Section (8 blocks)
  1) Bottom Layer: Two red arches (side by side).  
  2) Second Layer: One horizontal yellow plank bridging across the two arches.  
  3) Third Layer: Three blocks across—green cube on the left, tall blue rectangular block in the center, green cube on the right.  
  4) Fourth Layer: A single small blue cube placed on top (center).  
  5) Fifth/Top Layer: An orange triangular “roof” wedge resting on the blue cube.

• Right Section (12 blocks)
  1) Bottom Layer: Three red arches lined up.  
  2) Second Layer: One horizontal yellow plank bridging those three arches.  
  3) Upper Pieces (placed on or just above the yellow plank):
     – One small blue cube toward the left  
     – Two yellow half‐cylinders (side by side)  
     – Two tall vertical yellow blocks standing at or near center/back  
     – One short green rectangular block, one tall green rectangular block (behind or beside the others)  
     – One orange cube on the right side.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2.  SELECTING THE DICTIONARY BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Matching each visible block exactly (shape, color, and orientation) yields the following indices from your dictionary:

• Red arches (front‐facing): index 1  
  – 5 total arches needed (2 on the left section, 3 on the right)  

• Horizontal yellow rectangular plank: index 10  
  – 2 total (one bridging the 2 arches on the left, one bridging the 3 arches on the right)  

• Green cubes: index 4  
  – 2 total (both are the small green cubes in the middle layer on the left)  

• Tall blue rectangular block (vertical): index 7  
  – 1 total (center of the left section’s third layer)  

• Small blue cubes: index 3  
  – 2 total (one at the top of the left section, one on the right section)  

• Orange wedge (the “roof” piece): index 16  
  – 1 total (very top of the left section)  

• Yellow half‐cylinders: index 13  
  – 2 total (front row of curved pieces on the right section)  

• Tall yellow rectangular blocks (vertical): index 11  
  – 2 total (the two tall upright yellow columns on the right)  

• Short green rectangular block: index 8  
  – 1 total (right section, smaller green rectangular piece)  

• Tall green rectangular block: index 9  
  – 1 total (right section, taller green block near the orange cube)  

• Orange cube: index 5  
  – 1 total (right section, on top/right)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3.  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
A simple bottom‐to‐top build order follows.  Use the exact block indices listed:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 1   (first red arch, left section)
  Step2:  Move block with index 1   (second red arch, left section)
  Step3:  Move block with index 10  (yellow plank bridging those two arches)
  Step4:  Move block with index 4   (left green cube on third layer)
  Step5:  Move block with index 7   (tall blue rectangle in center)
  Step6:  Move block with index 4   (right green cube on third layer)
  Step7:  Move block with index 3   (blue cube on top)
  Step8:  Move block with index 16  (orange wedge roof)

  Step9:  Move block with index 1   (first red arch, right section)
  Step10: Move block with index 1   (second red arch, right section)
  Step11: Move block with index 1   (third red arch, right section)
  Step12: Move block with index 10  (yellow plank across those three arches)
  Step13: Move block with index 3   (blue cube on left side of plank)
  Step14: Move block with index 13  (first yellow half‐cylinder)
  Step15: Move block with index 13  (second yellow half‐cylinder)
  Step16: Move block with index 11  (first tall yellow upright)
  Step17: Move block with index 11  (second tall yellow upright)
  Step18: Move block with index 8   (short green rectangular block)
  Step19: Move block with index 9   (tall green rectangular block)
  Step20: Move block with index 5   (orange cube on the right)
}

Following these steps (or any other systematic bottom‐to‐top approach) will reproduce the target structure exactly as shown.
